# Refactor Pass — DRY Cleanup for Game Boards

## Why

The `src/play/boards/` directory has accumulated significant code duplication
across the different game-mode board components (X01Board, BattleBoard,
KillerBoard, HighScoreBoard, CardBoard). CardBoard.tsx alone is 810 lines.
The same patterns — power-up banner rendering, quit button, game-over guard,
dart slot rendering, scored calculation with power-up modifiers, turn-advance
with frozen-skip logic, reroll overlay wiring — are copy-pasted across 4-5
files. This makes bugs hard to fix (the same fix must be applied N times) and
makes the files harder to navigate.

## What we're doing

1. **Extract `PowerUpBanners` component** — the 6 power-up status banners
   (_oneDartNext, _crippledNext, _surgeNext, _bullseyeFrenzy, _hotStreak,
   _shieldTurns) are copy-pasted verbatim in X01Board, BattleBoard,
   KillerBoard, HighScoreBoard, and CardBoard. Extract to a single component
   in `src/play/common.tsx`.

2. **Extract `QuitButton` component** — the same quit button with confirm
   dialog appears in every board.

3. **Extract `GameOverGuard` component** — every board starts with
   `if (game.finished) return <GameOver .../>` with identical props.

4. **Extract `DartSlots` component** — the slot rendering logic (with
   power-up 4th-dart / 1-dart-next sizing) is duplicated.

5. **Extract `calcScored` helper** — the surge/cripple/bullseyeFrenzy/
   hotStreak scored calculation is duplicated in X01Board, BattleBoard,
   HighScoreBoard, and CardBoard (partially).

6. **Extract `clearVisitFlags` helper** — the pattern of deleting the
   one-visit power-up flags from the current player is duplicated.

7. **Extract `useRerollOverlay` hook** — the reroll state + resolve pattern
   is identical in X01Board, BattleBoard, KillerBoard, HighScoreBoard.

8. **Extract `advanceSimpleTurn` helper** — the simple turn-advance with
   frozen-skip + shield-tick logic (used by Battle, Killer, HighScore) is
   duplicated. X01 has a more complex version with team/leg logic that stays
   in-place but can share the frozen-skip portion.

9. **Extract `ScorePopups` helper** — the SCORE_POPUPS milestone check is
   duplicated in Battle, HighScore, and CardBoard.

10. **Split CardBoard.tsx** — Extract the card-pile popup (deck/graveyard
    viewer) and the card-detail popup into separate components, reducing
    CardBoard from ~810 lines to a more manageable size.

